				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, the number of counters removed is a function of wind modifier (and a little bit of level math in the case of Aria of Asceticism).
<br />

<br />
Without any instruments, Aria of Innocence is going to remove just 4 curse counters.  Since most curse effects are 9 curse counters minimum, you would need to sing it 3 times to remove the effect from a single target.
<br />

<br />
Now say you've got your first Epic, but you don't yet have any Instrument Mastery AA:  at that point you're going to remove 7 counters, so you'll still have to sing it twice.
<br />

<br />
But maybe you've got a Bloodstained Flute from some Named in Mistmoore Catacombs (2.2 mod, primary hand) and maybe you've bought 1 level of Instrument Mastery AA (+0.2) for a total mod of 2.4 -- well then you cure 9 curse counters per song. 
<br />

<br />
With a 3 second cast time and some quick-fingered targetting, you could get a lot of people cured in a short amount of time.  
<br />

<br />
Talk to your rogue friends about their new Epic fights and how you can help...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
